Later he ran to the front line and led his people forward with the "greatest courage" before he alone attacked an artillery and detonated three guns.
Lieutenant Colonel Vann was killed by a German sniper on October 4, 1918 – just a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann at 72 said that his grandfather's actions were "something I knew I could never live up to, but which humbles me."
